<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,624,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cothornobata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingensfurca">
<emphasis box="[325,624,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Cothornobata ingensfurca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs markedly from congeners by having a black fore tibia with a yellow tip, and a genital fork that is wider than the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,893,548,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="etymology">
